claim: South Sudan has the lowest access to electricity over the years among the given countries.
label: Supports
explanation: The chart illustrates the percentage of the population with access to electricity in various countries over a range of years. Upon examining the data presented, it is evident that South Sudan consistently displays the lowest percentage of access to electricity compared to other countries listed in the chart. This indicates that, throughout the years represented, South Sudan has struggled significantly more than its counterparts in providing electricity access to its population, which supports the claim that it has the lowest access to electricity.
